<h3>Description</h3>
<p>When using the global scope for parameters in procedures, 
the <b>pure</b> keyword can be added to force Turbo Rascal to 
check that the value passed is a variable or constant, but not an expression.</p>

<h3>Example</h3>

<code>

procedure DoSomething( myVar : global pure byte) inline; 
begin

end;

</code>

<h3>See also</h3>
<p>pure, pure_number, pure_variable</p>
